This paper is primarily focused on reinforcement learning with neural networks, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses game theory and optimization, which are relevant to cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). The proposed approach involves updating a single model with sub-models and a selector, which could be considered a form of ensemble learning, placing it under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the efficiency and robustness of the proposed approach, which could be relevant to cs.SY (Systems and Control).
